[{"kind":{"id":"E0001","name":"malformed-type-variable","expected":"type variable identifier (e.g., 'a, 'b)","found":{"kind":"comment","text":"(* hello *)"},"fix":"remove the space or comment between the quote and the variable name","hint":"Type variables must be written as 'a, 'b, etc. with no space or comments between the quote and name."},"span":{"start":6,"end":17}},{"kind":{"id":"E0001","name":"malformed-type-variable","expected":"type variable identifier (e.g., 'a, 'b)","found":{"kind":"whitespace","text":" "},"fix":"remove the space or comment between the quote and the variable name","hint":"Type variables must be written as 'a, 'b, etc. with no space or comments between the quote and name."},"span":{"start":26,"end":27}},{"kind":{"id":"E0001","name":"malformed-type-variable","expected":"type variable identifier (e.g., 'a, 'b)","found":{"kind":"'","text":"'"},"fix":"remove the space or comment between the quote and the variable name","hint":"Type variables must be written as 'a, 'b, etc. with no space or comments between the quote and name."},"span":{"start":36,"end":37}},{"kind":{"id":"E0022","name":"invalid-type-parameter","expected":"valid type parameter","found":{"kind":"@","text":"@"},"fix":"use a valid type parameter like 'a or _","hint":"Type parameters must start with a single quote followed by a lowercase letter.\n\nValid type parameters:\n  ```ocaml\n  type 'a t           (* correct: single lowercase type variable *)\n  type ('a, 'b) t     (* correct: multiple type variables *)\n  type _ t            (* correct: wildcard type parameter *)\n  ```\n\nInvalid type parameters:\n  ```ocaml\n  type __ t           (* error: use _ instead of __ *)\n  type @ t            (* error: @ is not valid *)\n  type ! t            (* error: ! is not valid *)\n  ```\n"},"span":{"start":58,"end":59}},{"kind":{"id":"E0022","name":"invalid-type-parameter","expected":"valid type parameter","found":{"kind":"!","text":"!"},"fix":"use a valid type parameter like 'a or _","hint":"Type parameters must start with a single quote followed by a lowercase letter.\n\nValid type parameters:\n  ```ocaml\n  type 'a t           (* correct: single lowercase type variable *)\n  type ('a, 'b) t     (* correct: multiple type variables *)\n  type _ t            (* correct: wildcard type parameter *)\n  ```\n\nInvalid type parameters:\n  ```ocaml\n  type __ t           (* error: use _ instead of __ *)\n  type @ t            (* error: @ is not valid *)\n  type ! t            (* error: ! is not valid *)\n  ```\n"},"span":{"start":68,"end":69}},{"kind":{"id":"E0022","name":"invalid-type-parameter","expected":"valid type parameter","found":{"kind":"^","text":"^"},"fix":"use a valid type parameter like 'a or _","hint":"Type parameters must start with a single quote followed by a lowercase letter.\n\nValid type parameters:\n  ```ocaml\n  type 'a t           (* correct: single lowercase type variable *)\n  type ('a, 'b) t     (* correct: multiple type variables *)\n  type _ t            (* correct: wildcard type parameter *)\n  ```\n\nInvalid type parameters:\n  ```ocaml\n  type __ t           (* error: use _ instead of __ *)\n  type @ t            (* error: @ is not valid *)\n  type ! t            (* error: ! is not valid *)\n  ```\n"},"span":{"start":78,"end":79}},{"kind":{"id":"E0022","name":"invalid-type-parameter","expected":"valid type parameter","found":{"kind":"[","text":"["},"fix":"use a valid type parameter like 'a or _","hint":"Type parameters must start with a single quote followed by a lowercase letter.\n\nValid type parameters:\n  ```ocaml\n  type 'a t           (* correct: single lowercase type variable *)\n  type ('a, 'b) t     (* correct: multiple type variables *)\n  type _ t            (* correct: wildcard type parameter *)\n  ```\n\nInvalid type parameters:\n  ```ocaml\n  type __ t           (* error: use _ instead of __ *)\n  type @ t            (* error: @ is not valid *)\n  type ! t            (* error: ! is not valid *)\n  ```\n"},"span":{"start":88,"end":89}},{"kind":{"id":"E0023","name":"uppercase-type-variable","expected":"lowercase type variable","found":{"kind":"identifier","text":"A"},"fix":"change A to a","hint":"Type variables must use lowercase letters.\n\nType variables in OCaml always start with a single quote followed by a lowercase identifier:\n  ```ocaml\n  type 'a t           (* correct *)\n  type 'myvar t       (* correct *)\n  type 'A t           (* error: must be lowercase *)\n  type 'MyType t      (* error: must be lowercase *)\n  ```\n\nFix: change 'A to 'a, or 'MyType to 'my_type\n"},"span":{"start":97,"end":99}}]
